         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Premier's Office, ¶ Melbourne, 4th November, 1895. ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ I am directed by the Premier to request that you will be pleased to grant to any employe's of your Department who are eligible, and may i...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.11.04a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Charles Topp</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No.5534, p. 920, unit 108, VPRS 1187/P, outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office of Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Document is a circular sent to the heads of 14 branches<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>within the Chief Secretary's Department.</p>
               </note>Premier's Office,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, 4th November, 1895.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am directed by the Premier to request that you will be pleased to grant to any employe's of your Department who are eligible, and may intend to compete at the Victorian Rifle Association Annual Matches to be held between the 18th and 23rd instant, the necessary leave of absence to admit of their doing so; provided the leave can be given without business being interfered with.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedient servant,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(Sigd.)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="text-transform: uppercase; ">Charles A. Topp</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
